==English==

===Etymology===
Old English [[ridan|rīdan]], from Germanic ''*ridanan'', from Indo-European ''*reidh-''. Cognate with Dutch [[rijden]], German [[reiten]], Swedish [[rida]]; and (''from Indo-European'') with Welsh [[rhwyddhau]] ‘hurry’.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/raɪd/}}, {{SAMPA|/raId/}}
*{{audio|en-us-ride.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*{{rhymes|aɪd}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|rides|riding|rode|ridden}}

# To [[transport]] oneself with a [[bicycle]], a [[horse]].
# To sit on and control an animal for sport or recreation.
# Be carried or supported by (something with momentum).

